Metro Pacific Gains, Snaps Four-Day Slump, on Hospital Purchase

-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-10-24T01:58:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-24/metro-pacific-gains-snaps-four-day-slump-on-hospital-purchase.html
Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI) 
climbed in  Manila , ending a four-day decline, after the company
said it bought the operator of Cardinal Santos Medical Center
for 300 million pesos ($6.92 million).  The stock advanced as much as 1.7 percent to 3.05 pesos and
traded at 3.03 pesos at 9:57 a.m. local time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Matthew Oakley at 
 moakley@bloomberg.net  